    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><div>The AmazonS3 module allows the drupal local file system to be replaced with S3, where the files can be uploaded or downloaded from S3. I used the following modules to achieve this:</div>
<ul><li>   <a href="http://www.drupal.org/project/amazons3">Amazon S3(module)</a></li>
<li>   <a href="http://www.drupal.org/project/libraries">Libraries API</a></li>
<li>   <a href="http://www.drupal.org/project/awssdk">AWSSDK for PHP(module)</a></li>
<li>   <a href="http://aws.amazon.com/sdkforphp">AWSSDK For PHP(library)</a>
<ul><li><strong>Note:</strong> Verify that SDK library meets your system requirements. Refer this: <a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/aws-sdk-php/guide/latest/requirements.html">http://docs.aws.amazon.com/aws-sdk-php/guide/latest/requirements.htm</a>l         </li>
</ul></li>
</ul><div> </div>
<div>Download and install these modules and place SDK library at sites/all/libraries/awssdk.</div>
<div>Check  'Status report'  for information about the installation of  AmazonS3 and AWSSDK.</div>
